.\" Man page for nlmgen
.TH NLMGEN 1 "December 2025" "nlmgen 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nlmgen \- NotebookLM Generation Tool for automated learning material creation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nlmgen
.I input
.RB [ \-e
.IR email ]
.RB [ \-p
.IR password ]
.RB [ \-o
.IR output ]
.RB [ \-\-api\-key
.IR key ]
.RB [ \-\-headless ]
.RB [ \-v ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nlmgen
is an automated tool that generates comprehensive learning materials from educational content using Google's Gemini AI and NotebookLM.
.PP
It takes a PDF, TXT file, or website URL as input and generates:
.IP \(bu 2
Video summaries via NotebookLM Audio Overview
.IP \(bu 2
Handouts with keypoint summaries
.IP \(bu 2
Cheatsheets for quick reference
.IP \(bu 2
Mindmaps in Mermaid diagram format
.IP \(bu 2
Audiobook chapter scripts
.IP \(bu 2
Fantasy and Sci-Fi stories that teach the concepts
.IP \(bu 2
Learning strategy papers for exam preparation
.IP \(bu 2
Flashcards (Karteikarten) in Markdown and Anki format
.IP \(bu 2
Quizzes with answer keys
.IP \(bu 2
Podium discussions with 3 participants
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I input
Input file path (PDF, TXT) or website URL to process. Required.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-email " " \fIemail\fR
Google account email for authentication.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-password " " \fIpassword\fR
Google account password. Use single quotes around passwords with special characters:
.BR "\-p 'my!password'" .
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIdirectory\fR
Output directory for generated files. Defaults to a folder named \fI<input>_output\fR in the same directory as the input file.
.TP
.BR \-\-api\-key " " \fIkey\fR
Gemini API key. Can also be set via the GEMINI_API_KEY environment variable.
.TP
.B \-\-headless
Run the browser in headless mode (no visible window). Not recommended when 2FA or passkey verification is required.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with additional debug information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.SH AUTHENTICATION
The tool requires a Google account to access NotebookLM and Gemini services. When running for the first time:
.IP 1. 3
Enter your Google email and password
.IP 2. 3
A browser window will open for login
.IP 3. 3
Complete any 2FA, passkey, or fingerprint verification in the browser
.IP 4. 3
The tool will continue automatically after verification
.PP
Session cookies are saved to
.I ~/.notebook_lm_gen/
for subsequent runs.
.SH OUTPUT STRUCTURE
Generated files are organized in subdirectories:
.PP
.nf
<input>_output/
\(ti\(ti videos/           # NotebookLM generated videos
\(ti\(ti handouts/         # Summary handouts
\(ti\(ti cheatsheets/      # Quick reference sheets
\(ti\(ti mindmaps/         # Mermaid diagram mindmaps
\(ti\(ti audiobooks/       # Narration scripts
\(ti\(ti stories/          # Fantasy & Sci-Fi stories
\(ti\(ti strategies/       # Learning strategy papers
\(ti\(ti flashcards/       # Markdown flashcards
\(ti\(ti anki/             # Anki deck files (.apkg, .txt)
\(ti\(ti quizzes/          # Quiz files with answer keys
\(ti\(ti discussions/      # Podium discussion scripts
\(ti\(ti notebook_lm_generation.log
.fi
.SH PROGRESS REPORTING
The tool displays progress updates every 15 seconds showing:
.IP \(bu 2
Current processing step
.IP \(bu 2
Completed vs total steps
.IP \(bu 2
Elapsed time
.IP \(bu 2
Status of each generation task
.SH EXAMPLES
Process a PDF file with Google authentication:
.PP
.nf
.RS
nlmgen document.pdf -e user@gmail.com -p 'password123!'
.RE
.fi
.PP
Process a website with API key:
.PP
.nf
.RS
nlmgen https://example.com/article --api-key YOUR_API_KEY
.RE
.fi
.PP
Process a text file with custom output directory:
.PP
.nf
.RS
nlmgen notes.txt -o ~/study_materials/
.RE
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GEMINI_API_KEY
Gemini API key for content generation. Get one from https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.notebook_lm_gen/google_cookies.pkl
Saved session cookies for Google authentication.
.TP
.I <install_dir>/.env
Configuration file for API keys and settings.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred during processing.
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
NotebookLM does not have an official API; the tool uses browser automation.
.IP \(bu 2
Audio/video generation can take several minutes per topic.
.IP \(bu 2
Passkey or 2FA verification must be completed manually in the browser.
.IP \(bu 2
The browser remains open after completion with Gemini loaded.
.IP \(bu 2
StudioAutomator supports batch generation of 6 material types per source.
.SH STUDIO AUTOMATION
The StudioAutomator class provides programmatic access to NotebookLM Studio features:
.IP \(bu 2
Audio Summary \- generates audio overview with English language
.IP \(bu 2
Video Overview \- generates video summary with English language
.IP \(bu 2
Mindmap \- generates visual mindmap (immediate)
.IP \(bu 2
Quiz \- generates interactive quiz (immediate)
.IP \(bu 2
Flashcards \- generates Karteikarten (immediate)
.IP \(bu 2
Infographic \- generates visual infographic with English language
.PP
Use \fBprocess_all_sources()\fR to generate all materials for all sources, or specify a subset with the \fBmaterials\fR parameter.
